<dl id="n08137f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08137f">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08137f"> 137(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ asked for 2<sup>d</sup> worth of toffee</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>A Terrible Swell</b> Martin Keely was found guilty, at the Dublin Commission yesterday, of having on Sept. 23, stolen from Mrs. M. Merriman, <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> a handbag containing &pound;2.12s., and a gold ring <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> She went into the sweet-shop for bread, and the prisoner followed, dressed like an earl, and <mark>asked for twopence worth of toffee</mark>. <small> <a name="II7feb24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#II7feb24"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (7 February 1924) 4/2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
